# Web Production Gates (`web/`)

Applies to all work under `web/`. Complements rule `60-zero-gate-health-check.mdc` and `71-git-discipline.mdc`.

## Homepage hero invariants (Next.js 16)

- **Exactly one** `"use client"` hero module: [`web/src/components/marketing/HomeHero.tsx`](web/src/components/marketing/HomeHero.tsx)
- It owns `Section`, motion root, viewport gate, and mobile/desktop variants
- **Never** split into server `HomeHero` + client `HomeHeroMotionShell` (or similar) — causes undefined lazy-element crashes
- **Never** import from `@/components/marketing/hero-motion` barrel — import source files only (ESLint enforced)
- **Never** add `"use client"` files that only re-export another hero module
- Homepage **must** mount hero through [`HomeHeroGate`](web/src/components/marketing/HomeHeroGate.tsx) + [`HomeHeroPlaceholder`](web/src/components/marketing/HomeHeroPlaceholder.tsx) so heavy hero chunks load after `window.load` (domcontentloaded resource budget ≤ 30)
- Below-fold homepage sections **must** mount through [`HomeBelowFoldGate`](web/src/components/marketing/HomeBelowFoldGate.tsx) with the same deferral helper ([`homepage-deferred-load.ts`](web/src/lib/homepage-deferred-load.ts))

## Before push (mandatory when user requests push)

From **repository root**:

```bash
npm run ci:check --prefix web
```

Or: `./web/scripts/verify-ci-parity.ps1`

- Exit code **must be 0** — matches [`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](.github/workflows/ci.yml) `lint-and-build` job
- **Do not push** if a background `ci:check` failed, was interrupted, or only partial checks ran (lint/typecheck/e2e subset)
- **Do not claim CI green** without GitHub Actions evidence on the pushed SHA (or state *local pass only — remote unverified*)

## Homepage-touching changes — required release gates

After any edit to hero, homepage layout, `page.tsx`, or homepage performance deferrals, the following must pass (included in `ci:check`):

1. `homepage renders without client runtime errors` — zero `pageerror`, `.hero-section` visible
2. `homepage resource budget stays within performance guardrails` — ≤ 30 resources at `domcontentloaded`

Read [`DOC/PROJECT PLAN/Tasks/tasks.md`](DOC/PROJECT PLAN/Tasks/tasks.md) Session Audit Log before hero or CI work — prior failures are documented there.

## Known CI failure modes

| Symptom | Gate / step | Typical fix |
|---------|-------------|-------------|
| Lazy element undefined at HomeHero | pageerror e2e | Single client `HomeHero.tsx`; no server-shell split |
| SSG `took more than N seconds` | `npm run build` | Raise `staticPageGenerationTimeout` in `next.config.ts`; avoid build-time Sanity thrashing |
| Resource count 31–39 | resource budget e2e | Defer SpeedInsights until `load`; `HomeHeroGate` + `HomeBelowFoldGate` schedule bundles after `window.load`; static `HomeHeroPlaceholder` keeps `.hero-section` for pageerror gate; poster-first hero |
| ESLint in ~1–2 min | `npm run lint` | Fix reported file; run full `ci:check`, not lint alone |

## Session start checklist (web/ CI or hero work)

1. Read `memories/repo/site-brain.md` → CI and pre-push parity
2. Read latest Session Audit Log in `DOC/PROJECT PLAN/Tasks/tasks.md`
3. Run full `ci:check --prefix web` before push — never substitute partial runs
